===Etymology===
Anastasia is a female given name which comes from Koine Greek. Its literal translation is "She who shall rise up again" although it is usually just referred to as meaning resurrection. The name, and its male counterpart, [[Anastasius]] were originally given to children who were born around Eastertime during the early years of Christianity.

The names "Stacey" (also spelled "Stacie", "Stacy" or "Stacee"), "Tasia", and "Stasia" (or "Statia") are derived from Anastasia.

